ng. In focus for this book is the relationship between history and cognition, the human mind’s interaction with the environment in time and space. It especially discusses certain cognitive abilities in interaction with the environment, which can be studied in historical sources, namely: evolution, language, rationality, spatiality, and materiality. Cognitive history can give us a deeper understanding of how – and not only what – people thought, and about the interaction between the human mind and the surrounding world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCognitionxHistory.1 aAhlberger, Christer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAhlberger, Christer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAllwood, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunér, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunér, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEriksson, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Rakel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSonesson, Göran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÅberg, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831105798400